_meanings:
{@--1@} (Intransitively used)
({%a%}) To shine, blaze (as fire or sun);
{#tamastapati GarmAMSO kaTamAvirBavizyati#}  
<ls>Ś. 5. 14</ls>; <ls>R. 5. 13</ls>; <ls>U. 6. 14</ls>; <ls>Bg. 9. 19.</ls>
({%b%}) To be hot or warm, give out
heat. ({%c%}) To suffer pain; {#tapati na#}
{#sA kisalayaSayanena#} <ls>Gīt. 7.</ls> ({%d%}) To
mortify the body, undergo penance
(with {#tapas#}); {#agaRitatanUta paM taptvA#}
{#tapAMsi BagIraTaH#} <ls>U. 1. 23.</ls>

{@--2@} 
(Transitively used) ({%a%}) To make hot,
heat, warm; <ls>Bk. 9. 2</ls>; <ls>Bg. 11. 19.</ls>
({%b%}) To inflame, burn, consume
by heat; {#tapati tanugAtri#} 
{#madanastvAmaniSaM mAM punardahatyeva#} <ls>Ś. 3. 17</ls>; {#aMgEranaMgataptEH#}
<ls n="Ś.">3. 7</ls>. ({%c%}) To hurt, injure, damage,
spoil; {#yAsyan sutastapyati mAM samanyuM#}
<ls>Bk. 1. 23</ls>; <ls>Ms. 7. 6.</ls> ({%d%}) To pain,
distress. ({%e%}) To mortify the body.
undergo penance (with {#tapas#})'

{@--1@} To heat, make warm;
{#gaganaM tApitapAyitAsilakzmIM#} <ls>Śi. 20. 75</ls>; {#na#}
{#hi tApayituM SakyaM sAgarAMBastfRolkayA#}  
<ls>H. 1. 86.</ls>
